  "prompt": "When the Night King's White Walkers take children, do they become fully grown like those at end of the Game of Thrones episode \"Oathbreaker?\"",
  "response": "In the \"Game of Thrones\" series, when the Night King transforms a human into a White Walker, the transformation process is not fully detailed. However, we do see one significant instance of this transformation in the episode \"Oathbreaker\" from Season 6.\n\nIn this episode, the Night King touches an infant, Craster's son, and the baby's eyes turn blue, indicating the transformation into a White Walker. The transformed baby is not shown again until much later in the series, in the episode \"The Door\" from Season 6. Here, we see the child as a fully grown White Walker, suggesting that the transformation not only changes the child into a White Walker but also accelerates their aging to that of an adult.\n\nThis implies that when children are taken and transformed by the Night King, they do indeed become fully grown White Walkers, as observed in the series. However, the exact mechanics and timeline of this transformation remain somewhat mysterious, consistent with the show's portrayal of the White Walkers as enigmatic and otherworldly beings.",
